issue.title: Create Appointment "Scheduled Time" date picker issue
issue.body:
### Information about bug

- When trying to create a new "Appointment"
- Click on "Scheduled Time" the time picker will as seen below "undefined, NaN".
- But  if we click "Now" then try to open the picker again it will be fine.


![Screenshot 2023-10-03 005009](https://github.com/frappe/erpnext/assets/29341232/ee17228f-73f1-476e-9241-c201e44e66c4)

am using the demo trail from the frappe website it self so am using the latest version i guess.

### Module

CRM

### Version

ERPNext: v15.0.0-dev (HEAD)
Frappe Framework: v15.0.0-dev (HEAD)

### Installation method

FrappeCloud

### Relevant log output / Stack trace / Full Error Message.

_No response_

comment.body:
That may be a workaround, @moaazmf90, but certainly isn’t a fix.
Even initializing it with `Now` shouldn’t actually be necessary.

It shouldn’t be all too hard to fix, but I need to find some time to investigate what’s wrong here.
In the meantime, feel free to look into the datepicker’s implementation for a missing fallback value.

issue.title: fix: Allow creating Item as is_fixed_asset in Quick Entry.
issue.body:
`is_fixed_asset` currently wasn‘t included in the Quick Entry form.
As the field is `set_only_once` and the doc is being saved, there‘s no way to check the box later.
Effectively, it currently isn‘t possible to create a fixed asset via the Quick Entry form.

Fixing this was slightly less straightforward than expected, but in the second revision could be sufficiently solved:

1. Obviously `is_fixed_asset` had to be added to Quick Entry. 
2. However, Asset Category is mandatory for Fixed Assets, so needs to be added too if we don‘t want to leave the Item in an incorrect state.
3. Now, `is_fixed_asset` and `is_stock_item` are mutually exclusive. An informed decision in the Quick Entry form is only possible if we‘re adding the latter as well, so people can easily grasp the mutual exclusivity and choose one or the other.
4. If need be, `is_stock_item` may stay _on_ by default, so `is_fixed_asset` is initially disabled. To enable `is_fixed_asset`, you first need to disable `is_stock_item`. That’s halfway acceptable. However, `is_stock_item` should not bounce back when disabling`is_fixed_asset` again.
5. Regarding the full form: showing/enabling and hiding/disabling quite distant, mutually exclusive checkboxes is rather confusing. I‘m therefore moving `is_fixed_asset` together with its dependent fields to the top, so it is closer to `is_stock_item`. With the two mutually exclusive fields next to each other from the start, the mutual exclusivity is way easier to grasp.

https://github.com/frappe/erpnext/assets/46800703/2d99140c-4e88-4464-8417-0a49ac803081

All in all, I think this revised approach is a clear UX improvement and a good compromise, particularly if the tests are passing, so BC is given. In a followup we may discuss whether `is_stock_item` should be _on_ by default or not.

It also fixes #37505.

comment.body:
I‘m just wondering whether my last proposal may actually be perfectly compatible with @s-aga-r‘s proposal, while being quite a bit out of scope of the actual bugfix.

I‘ll start implementing the former, and may then launch a followup issue. 👍
